## Summary

The issue was an incorrect signaling procedure sequence in the `rrc_M2AP_do_SIB23_SIB13` function (line 882) that violated 3GPP message flow requirements for MBMS configuration.

### Problem
When SIB13 was configured separately from SIB2, the MAC layer wasn't receiving all necessary parameters, specifically:
1. Missing `MBMS_flag` initialization
2. Missing MBSFN subframe configuration list (from SIB2)
3. Missing FeMBMS flag
4. Missing proper RNTI configuration

### Solution
Added complete MAC layer configuration in `rrc_M2AP_do_SIB23_SIB13` to match the combined function `rrc_M2AP_do_SIB23_SIB2_SIB13`:

```c
carrier->MBMS_flag = 1;

rrc_mac_config_req_eNB_t tmp = {0};
tmp.CC_id = CC_id;
tmp.rnti = 0xfffd;
tmp.mbsfn_SubframeConfigList = carrier->sib2->mbsfn_SubframeConfigList;
tmp.MBMS_Flag = carrier->MBMS_flag;
tmp.mbsfn_AreaInfoList = &carrier->sib13->mbsfn_AreaInfoList_r9;
tmp.FeMBMS_Flag = carrier->FeMBMS_flag;
rrc_mac_config_req_eNB(Mod_id, &tmp);
```

This ensures proper 3GPP-compliant signaling flow when SIB13 is configured independently, as the MAC layer now receives all required MBMS parameters in the correct sequence.

